The paper deals with image generation tasks, specifically predicting shading fields and adjusting image saturation and relighting. This suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, such as variational autoencoders, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of quantitative metrics to evaluate results, which suggests a focus on graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
